data.reasoningText:
Now I have a good understanding of the project. Let me plan and implement.

## Component Plan: Kanban Board

### Component Tree
```
KanbanBoard (page — owns all data, route /board)
├── BoardSummaryBar (stats: total, per-column counts, overdue)
├── TaskSearchBar (search input, fires OnSearchChanged)
└── KanbanColumn (×3: To Do, In Progress, Done)
    ├── TaskCard (per task — title, assignee, priority badge, due date, move buttons)
    └── AddTaskForm (inline form for creating tasks)


```

The KanbanBoard component manages all the state—tasks, search filters, loading, and errors—then distributes the data down the tree. The summary bar gets the full unfiltered task list for accurate counts, while the search bar and columns receive filtered results. Task cards emit move events back up to the board, and the inline add form creates new tasks through a callback.

I'm planning the implementation order starting with the leaf components and working up: TaskCard, AddTaskForm, KanbanColumn, BoardSummaryBar, TaskSearchBar, then the main KanbanBoard page. I'll organize them in a Components/Board/ folder to keep things clean and make sure they're discoverable through the existing namespace setup.

